title: H
body:
She can feel the warm sunlight on her cheeks as it filters through the elongated branches of the flowering dogwood tree she sat under, the warm breeze smelling of freshly cut grass, the sound of children playing in the distance. Yn never was much of a summer girl but spring, spring well it was just the perfect middle ground. Not to hot, not to cold, just right. There was the small fact that her birthday always fell on spring break which was always nice during yn’s schooling years. She sat there contemplating life, occasionally taking a sip out of her water bottle. Unbeknownst to her there was a man sitting on a bench 30 feet away clutching dickens between his ring clad fingers, similarly contemplating about his life and wondering in what direction it should go next.

Yn never was one for over thinking things, but this wasn’t just your average situation that she had gotten herself into. Her father who she hadn’t ever had the best relationship with had recently contacted her. It was the first time in years he had reached out to her. Yn had cut him out of her life for a reason. She decided that she would worry later and go feed her sugar addiction for now. The bakery was a short walk from the park as well as yn’s flat. Convenient for her due to the fact that she was addicted to their chocolate chip cookies. The same man from the park was also headed to the bakery to pick up a small cake for his best friends birthday. Isn’t it strange how you can be so close yet so far from someone. Its like missed connections. Constantly crossing paths yet never fully meeting one another. Living in New York City this was an easy thing to do. So disheveled and over crowded, you could walk past your soulmate every day yet never notice due to all of the passing faces.

Should i continue?

title: i raise you........nipple piercing!harry
body:
[a tiny sneakity peakity]

Harry pushed himself up off of the cushions to sit beside you, coyly looking in your direction.

“C’mere.”

You stood no chance against the puppy-dog eyes and fell a fool to his outstretched arms. His chest was warm and his grip tight around your shoulders, an endearing thumb circling over the hem of your t-shirt. It was a place you felt comfortable; Harry’s arms, and you found yourself longing for them more and more as your friendship matured. It wasn’t something you’d seen coming.

His chest rose and fell, taking you with it in the same way gentle waves rocked a boat out at sea. The reliable and constant motion had lulled you to sleep more than once, but the combination of his warm touch and the drink you’d been nursing all night made it ever harder to suppress the urge to—

“When did y’get those done?” Harry interrupted.

You snapped to attention. “What?”

He moved a hand to your ear, taking notice to your piercings. A single finger traced the shape your ear, starting at your cartilage, and pit-stopped at each stud until he reached your earlobe.

“Your ears,” he paused at the small hoop decorating your orbital. “How’d y’decide to, um… get all of those done?”

You turned toward him, “Are you just trying to get me to ask about your piercing story?”

“No—!”

“—because I’ve heard it before, you dolt,” you said, laughing. “It’s your favorite drunk story. A party trick, if you will.”

Harry muttered something about a ‘show-off’ under his breath. “Was askin’ because I was curious, y/n, not to tell y’about how I’ve stabbed a needle through my own ear.”

You pushed away from his arms, fully facing him this time.

“Well then,” the smallest tinge of tension hummed in the space between you; if you hadn’t been buzzed yourself it likely would have gone unnoticed. “What do you want to know?” 

The wheels spun in Harry’s head; the way he squinted an eye in your direction, paused for a beat or two, licked at his lips before continuing. It told everything you needed to know.

“Haven’t you done a piercing or two?”

“Mhm,” you reached for your glass on the table, taking a drink before continuing. “A few friends asked me in college. Why?”

“What were they?”

You had to pause and think: “Um… I’ve definitely done a lobe or two. I also think someone had me help re-pierce their nose because they knew I had the right type of needles.”

Harry scoffed, “You had needles? Just lyin’ around?”

“I bought them and a pair of clamps,” you shrugged as if it wasn’t anything out of the ordinary. Between styling your friends’ hair, dying it odd colors, or even giving someone bangs at one point, cosmetic changes didn’t phase you. The only thing that hadn’t been crossed off of your ‘list’ was a stick n’ poke… that you’d remembered, at least.

“I’m pretty sure I still have a pack or two up in my room, still sealed and everything. Maybe even a set of barbells.”

Harry’s attempts to conceal his laughter were pitiful. He shook his head, growing more amused as every second passed.

“What is your problem?!” A less-than playful shove emphasized the last word of your question.

“Never would have pegged you as a professional piercer, is all.”

“I went to a party school, Harry,” you rolled your eyes, “Not a piercing apprenticeship.”

“Same difference.”

Harry’s attempts to conceal his laughter were pitiful. He shook his head, growing more amused as every second passed.

“What is your problem?!” A less-than playful shove emphasized the last word of your question.

“Never would have pegged you as a professional piercer, is all.”

“I went to a party school, Harry,” you rolled your eyes, “Not a piercing apprenticeship.”

“Same difference.”

[a tiny sneakity peakity]

Harry pushed himself up off of the cushions to sit beside you, coyly looking in your direction.

“C’mere.”

You stood no chance against the puppy-dog eyes and fell a fool to his outstretched arms. His chest was warm and his grip tight around your shoulders, an endearing thumb circling over the hem of your t-shirt. It was a place you felt comfortable; Harry’s arms, and you found yourself longing for them more and more as your friendship matured. It wasn’t something you’d seen coming.

His chest rose and fell, taking you with it in the same way gentle waves rocked a boat out at sea. The reliable and constant motion had lulled you to sleep more than once, but the combination of his warm touch and the drink you’d been nursing all night made it ever harder to suppress the urge to—

“When did y’get those done?” Harry interrupted.

You snapped to attention. “What?”

He moved a hand to your ear, taking notice to your piercings. A single finger traced the shape your ear, starting at your cartilage, and pit-stopped at each stud until he reached your earlobe.

“Your ears,” he paused at the small hoop decorating your orbital. “How’d y’decide to, um… get all of those done?”

You turned toward him, “Are you just trying to get me to ask about your piercing story?”

“No—!”

“—because I’ve heard it before, you dolt,” you said, laughing. “It’s your favorite drunk story. A party trick, if you will.”

Harry muttered something about a ‘show-off’ under his breath. “Was askin’ because I was curious, y/n, not to tell y’about how I’ve stabbed a needle through my own ear.”

You pushed away from his arms, fully facing him this time.

“Well then,” the smallest tinge of tension hummed in the space between you; if you hadn’t been buzzed yourself it likely would have gone unnoticed. “What do you want to know?” 

The wheels spun in Harry’s head; the way he squinted an eye in your direction, paused for a beat or two, licked at his lips before continuing. It told everything you needed to know.

“Haven’t you done a piercing or two?”

“Mhm,” you reached for your glass on the table, taking a drink before continuing. “A few friends asked me in college. Why?”

“What were they?”

You had to pause and think: “Um… I’ve definitely done a lobe or two. I also think someone had me help re-pierce their nose because they knew I had the right type of needles.”

Harry scoffed, “You had needles? Just lyin’ around?”

“I bought them and a pair of clamps,” you shrugged as if it wasn’t anything out of the ordinary. Between styling your friends’ hair, dying it odd colors, or even giving someone bangs at one point, cosmetic changes didn’t phase you. The only thing that hadn’t been crossed off of your ‘list’ was a stick n’ poke… that you’d remembered, at least.

“I’m pretty sure I still have a pack or two up in my room, still sealed and everything. Maybe even a set of barbells.”

Harry’s attempts to conceal his laughter were pitiful. He shook his head, growing more amused as every second passed.

“What is your problem?!” A less-than playful shove emphasized the last word of your question.

“Never would have pegged you as a professional piercer, is all.”

“I went to a party school, Harry,” you rolled your eyes, “Not a piercing apprenticeship.”

“Same difference.”

blog.title: Harry Is King Of Camp
blog.description:
Of all the sweet dreams Harry takes the cake.

Just a girl named Ellie in love

with a boy named Harry.

Masterlist

body:
Can’t Believe It

Just a little post-Met soft Harry bc I’m still so soft over him and the gala

“Babe c’mon it’s time.” You tried to coax.

“Whaaat no, love the party just started” Harry whines at you. You can’t help but smile at the drunken haze in his eyes. Eyes that aren’t even fully open.

“Babe it’s 5 am the party started and ended a long time ago.” You put his arm around your shoulder and wrap an arm around his waist to guide him. You look towards Kendall who gives you a laugh.

“Are you sure you don’t need any help Y/N” she asks collecting her purse.

“Ken, tell her we gotta keep partying!” Harry mumbles head bobbing to the side.

“I don’t know about that Harry, I’d listen to your girlfriend on this one.” She giggles

You smile at her shaking your head, “We’ll be fine but thank you.”

She laughs and walks to you planting a kiss on your cheek, “Well it was so good to see you, hopefully we can catch up soon,” she looks toward Harry, “and hopefully sober.”

You laugh and nod, “Definitely sober, text us when you get home please!” you insist. She nods and makes her way toward the door. A now sleeping Harry suddenly feels heavier and you fall on the couch with a huff. You take his arm off your shoulders and move to stand in front of him patting his face softly.

“My love c’mon you gotta get up, the car is waiting outside.” you shake his shoulder but no luck.

“Haaarry” you insist shaking a little harder. His eyes snap open.

“Y/N!” he exclaims, “My peaches, my love, my life” he sighs dreamily head bobbing once again.

You blush and you can swear your heart skipped a beat, “Get up baby we gotta go.” You tug a little on his arm to get up and he lifts his body up. You once again wrap his arm around your shoulders and grab his waist.

“This was the best night ever can you believe it?” he mumbles tapping your shoulder where his hand hangs.

“Of course I can believe, you’re brilliant and you did so well I’m so proud of you.” You place a little kiss on his hand next to your face.

He sighs and lies his head on yours as you walk out the door of the hotel awkwardly avoiding paparazzi and getting him into the car.

You release a breath as you finally rest in your seat and the driver pulls away. Harry still not all there conscious but enough to keep a tight grip on your hand.

“Can’t believe that actually ‘appened” he whispers eyes shut. You smile fondly and place a palm on his cheek.

“You were incredible tonight, don’t think I could love you any more.” You say rubbing his cheek.

He leans into your hand “Non, bunny don’t think I could love you any more, thanks for being here.”
